\f1\b0\fs60 \cf0 Preheat oven to 400 degrees F.\
Line a rimmed baking sheet with heavy foil. Place a baking rack over the lined sheet tray and arrange the bacon slices across the rack next to each other, not overlapping.\
In a small bowl, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whisk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 whisk}} the maple syrup and mustard. Generously spoon over the top of the bacon, and bake 12 to 15 minutes. Turn the bacon over and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/baste/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 baste}} with syrup mixture. Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes, or until the bacon has reached desired crispiness.\
Carefully remove the pan from the oven. Sprinkle hot bacon with a scant {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pinch/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pinch}} of finely ground black pepper. Let the bacon rest on the rack for 5 minutes.}